question.body: This question resolves **Yes** if, following the date of this question's publication and before May 1, 2024, credible reports indicate that an attack attributed to Iran and occurring within Israel's borders has led to the death of at least five individuals.

para_P.body: This inquiry will be resolved as **Yes** if, after the publication date of this question and before May 1, 2024, reliable reports emerge that an assault linked to Iran, taking place within the territory of Israel, has resulted in the fatalities of no fewer than five people.

para_P.body: This inquiry will receive a **Yes** response if, following the release date of this question and prior to May 1, 2024, there are trustworthy accounts of an assault associated with Iran occurring within the territory of Israel that leads to the fatalities of at least five individuals.

question.title: Will USA top the Olympic Medal Table at Paris 2024?
question.body:
This question will resolve positively if the United States Olympic Team are the (unique) highest ranked team at the 2024 Paris Olympics. It will resolve ambiguously if the Paris Olympics do not take place before 2027. It will resolve negatively if any team achieves a higher or equal ranking to the US team.

The medal table is calculated by taking all the medals won by each participating country and ordering by:

1. Number of Gold Medals
2. (Where 1 is tied) Number of Silver Medals
3. (Where 2 is tied) Number of Bronze Medals

question.title: Will OpenAI's ChatGPT be generally available in the European Union on June 30, 2024?
question.body:
The question resolves as **YES** if [ChatGPT](chat.openai.com) is generally available in the EU on June 30, 2024, and **NO** otherwise.

"Generally available" here means that the default state for people in the EU is that they can access it without a VPN (possibly requiring paying for it.) If unavailable in certain EU countries (as was the case in Italy in early 2023), or unavailable to (for example) minors, this will still resolve positively, assuming at least >50% of the population can use it.

"ChatGPT" here refers to the general web interface (not the API) for interacting with GPT models. Still resolves positively if the name or website has changed, as long as OpenAI's service is substantially the same (entering queries to systems based on Large Language Models).

question.title: Will the maximum weekly rate of hospitalizations per 100,000 in the US occur within four weeks of the combined peak for each of COVID, influenza, and RSV in the 2023-24 season?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if the maximum weekly rate of hospitalizations per 100,000 for each of COVID, influenza, and RSV that occurs in the 2023-24 season is less than or equal to four weeks (28 days) from the date of the maximum rate for all three combined, according to the CDC's [RESP-NET](https://www.cdc.gov/surveillance/resp-net/dashboard.html). The four weeks will be based on the week end dates. The CDC uses "epidemiological weeks" which begin on Sunday and end on Saturday. The rate used will be that for all ages, races, and sexes. See the fine print for the correct filters. For the purposes of this question, the 2023-2024 season will be considered to begin with the week ending on October 7, 2023, and end on the week ending June 1, 2024.

To allow for data revisions and reporting delays the question will resolve according to data shown after the reporting delay period, when the relevant figures for the current season is not shown as a dashed line, typically 4 weeks after the week end date.

question.title: Stranded astronauts depart on Boeing Starliner by July 21?
question.body:
Clone of (and resolves identically to) https://polymarket.com/event/stranded-astronauts-depart-on-boeing-starliner-by-july-21?tid=1719805056151

The Boeing Starliner spacecraft, which arrived at the ISS on June 6, 2024, with NASA astronauts Suni Williams and Butch Wilmore, must depart within 45 days due to the Harmony module's limited fuel.

This market will resolve to "Yes" if the Boeing Starliner spacecraft departs the International Space Station (ISS) with NASA astronauts Suni Williams and Butch Wilmore by 11:59 PM ET on July 21, 2024. 

The Starliner will be considered to have departed if it has undocked from the ISS and begun its return journey to Earth.

The resolution source will be official announcements from NASA and/or Boeing, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

not_P.body:

The Starliner will be considered to have not departed if it has not undocked from the ISS and begun its return journey to Earth.

The resolution source will be official announcements from NASA and/or Boeing, however a consensus of credible reporting may also be used.

question.title: Will France place in the Top 5 at the 2024 Paris Olympics?
question.body:

1. Number of Gold Medals

question.title: Will Deadpool & Wolverine have biggest opening weekend ever for R-rated movie? [ahead of Deadpool I & II, It, Joker]
question.body:
Analysts are projecting a huge opening weekend for "Deadpool x Wolverine" crossover movie.
https://deepnewz.com/movies/deadpool-wolverine-set-record-360m-global-opening-weekend-biggest-r-rated-debut

"""

The film, directed by Shawn Levy and starring Ryan Reynolds, is projected to earn between $340 million and $360 million globally in its opening weekend. This would mark the biggest opening weekend ever for an R-rated movie. Domestically, the film is expected to debut with $160 million to $170 million, making it the biggest R-rated opening of all-time.

"""

[image]The record for biggest opening weekend for an R-rated movie is the original Deadpool at $284.5M ($152.2M domestic).

https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/box-office-deadpool-makes-history-865143/

[image]
Will the new movie top these marks? It will probably be close...

It will certainly play at more theaters... Deadpool was a smash hit at the time, and a bit surprising.

Since BoxOfficeMojo is a bit weird on reporting international opening weekends -- it provides the raw numbers but aggregates them weirdly -- we will wait for Hollywood Reporter to let us know what the weekend opening was.

To clarify on resolution...
-> this market will resolve YES if Deadpool x Wolverine grosses more than $284.5M globally this opening weekend according to reports
-> AND the Hollywood Reporter (or equivalent publication) reports it as the record for an R-rated movie release

In other words the BoxOfficeMojo numbers should be seen as unofficial until there's confirmation in the Hollywood press. And the number we shoot for is >$284.5M internationally... this weekend

question.title: Will diplomatic expulsions or recalls take place between the Philippines and China before August 1, 2024?
question.body:
This question resolves as **Yes** if before August 1, 2024, one of these four events happens, according to official statements or [credible reports](https://www.metaculus.com/help/faq/#definitions): 

- The Philippines expels at least one diplomat representing the People's Republic of China (PRC). 

- The Philippines recalls at least one of its diplomats stationed in the PRC.

- The PRC expels at least one diplomat representing the Philippines.

- The PRC recalls at least one of its diplomats stationed in the Philippines. 

If there are no such reports before that date, then this resolves as **No**.

question.title: Facing Joe Biden instead of a generic Democrat, will Trump gain at least 3% among Manifold respondents?
question.body:
There are two Manifold polls posted, which both close on July 6.  One of the polls asks Manifold respondents to vote with Joe Biden on a hypothetical ballot, and another asks respondents to vote with a generic Democrat on the hypothetical ballot.

@/SteveSokolowski/1-of-2-given-these-choices-who-woul@/SteveSokolowski/2-of-2-given-these-choices-who-woul 

Public opinion polls consistently show Joe Biden losing to Donald Trump outside the margin of error, but every other Democrat hypothetically surveyed polls ahead or within the margin of error.  Are Manifold respondents representative of the general public?

This market will resolve YES if the percentage of votes for Donald Trump in poll 1 exceeds that in poll 2 by 3% or more when both polls close.

The formula for determining the percentage of votes for Trump is (Trump / (Trump + (the Democrat in the question) + Someone else)).  The answer is YES if this formula for poll 1 - the formula for poll 2 >= 0.03.  Otherwise, it is NO.

The polls and this question will never resolve N/A, and will remain open until the close time no matter what.

question.title: Will Glenn Youngkin be the Republican nominee for the 2024 US Presidential Election?
question.body:

All other candidates will resolve as **No**. This question is not restricted to the candidates currently listed; other options may be added in the future.

For this question, it is not relevant who receives the Republican nomination on the day of the 2024 US election; it is solely determined by who is selected by the delegates of the [Republican National Convention](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republican_National_Convention).

question.title: Will a group of at least 5 named Dem House Members or US Senators pressure Biden to drop out before July 20th?
question.body:
Politico reports:

Two safe-seat members have already publicly urged Biden out. Two of the most endangered Democrats told local news outlets they’ve already written off Biden’s chances to win in November.

Behind the scenes, things are even more frenzied. There are multiple drafts of letters circulating among House Democrats and at least one would call on Biden to end his campaign, according to five people familiar with the efforts.

This market resolves YES if a group of at least five named Democratic Party US House Members/US Senators work together to ask Joe Biden to consider ending his 2024 re-election campaign, or to urge him to do so, before Saturday July 20th (Pacific Time).

This could be by signing a letter like what is reported above, but it could also be in another form such as a group speaking with Biden in person and collectively asking him to drop out.

This market requires that all five individuals be part of the same group message. Five people separately telling reporters they think Biden should drop out is not sufficient for a YES resolution.

Reports of any number of unnamed democrats writing to Biden and asking him to step aside will not satisfy this market's criteria unless at least 5 qualifying names are later made public before this market's end date. In any ambiguous cases where such names are reported but not confirmed beyond a reasonable doubt, this market will err towards resolving NO. 

If these criteria are not met before July 20th, this market resolves NO.

This could be by signing a letter like what is reported above, but it could also be in another form such as a group speaking with Biden in person and collectively asking him to drop out.

This market requires that all five individuals not be part of the same group message. Five people separately telling reporters they think Biden should drop out is not sufficient for a YES resolution.

In any ambiguous cases where such names are reported but not confirmed beyond a reasonable doubt, this market will err towards resolving YES. 

If these criteria are not met before July 20th, this market resolves YES.

This could occur through signing a letter similar to the one mentioned above, or through another method, such as a group meeting with Biden in person and collectively requesting him to withdraw.

It is necessary for all five individuals to be part of a unified group communication. If five individuals separately inform reporters of their belief that Biden should withdraw, this will not be adequate for a YES resolution.

Reports of any number of unnamed Democrats reaching out to Biden and requesting him to step down will not meet the criteria for this market unless a minimum of five qualifying names are disclosed publicly before the market's closing date. In cases where names are reported but not confirmed with high certainty, this market will lean towards resolving NO.

If these conditions are not fulfilled by July 20th, this market will resolve to NO.

question.title: Will Donald Trump Jr. be the Republican nominee for the 2024 US Presidential Election?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if Donald Trump Jr. is selected by the Republican National Convention as the nominee for the 2024 US Presidential Election. All other candidates will resolve as **No**. This question is not restricted to the candidates currently mentioned; other options may be added in the future.

For this question, it is not relevant who receives the Republican nomination on the day of the 2024 US election; it is solely determined by who is selected by the delegates of the [Republican National Convention](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republican_National_Convention).

question.title: Will Russian athletes be barred from competing at the 2024 Olympics?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if Russian athletes are barred from competing at the 2024 Olympics under either (i) the Russian flag, (ii) The Russian Olympic Committee's flag, or (iii) any other independent or neutral flag. This will resolve based on the official list of countries and athletes present at the [2024 Olympics](https://olympics.com/en/olympic-games/paris-2024) or based on credible media reports, indicating that the 2024 Olympics are underway or have concluded without Russian participation. For the question to resolve as **Yes**, no more than 34 Russians can be competing at the 2024 Olympics. 34 was chosen as 10% of [Russian athletes that participated in the 2020 Olympics](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_Olympic_Committee_athletes_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics) to allow for a few individual or sport specific exceptions.

If more than 34 Russian athletes compete at the 2024 Olympics, this question will resolve as **No**.

If the 2024 Olympics are cancelled or postponed to 2025 or afterwards, this question resolves as ambiguously.

If 34 or fewer Russian athletes compete at the 2024 Olympics, this question will resolve as **No**.

If the 2024 Olympics are cancelled or postponed to 2025 or afterwards, this question resolves as ambiguously.

question.title: Will Joe Biden have an in-person interview/conversation on camera for 45+ minutes, before the end of July 2024?
question.body:
The most recent qualifying interview was Biden's appearance on The Howard Stern Show in April, when Biden answered questions for ~70 minutes. 

If Biden appears in another such in-person interview for at least 45 minutes, this market resolves YES. If no qualifying interview is released before market close at the end of July, this market resolves NO. 

This market does not include press conferences, speeches, rallies, fundraisers, town halls, etc. It can include appearances on a podcast or late night show, or an interview edited into a show like 60 minutes. However, there must be at least 45 minutes of new footage of Biden being interviewed in-person for such appearances to count. A 50 minute video might only feature 20 minutes of video of Biden being interviewed, and so would not count.

For context, Biden's interview with Stephanopoulos in July, his appearance on Jimmy Fallon in February, and his past appearances on 60 minutes have each had less than 30 minutes of video footage of Biden being interviewed. 

You can find a list of Biden's interviews and their transcripts here.

question.body:

question.title: Did someone intentionally shoot at Trump on July 13th?
question.body:
NYT: "It sounded what could be gun shots interrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was hurried off the stage and appeared to be bleeding by his ear."

Resolves YES if someone intentionally shot a bullet or other bullet-like projectile* at Trump on July 13th. Resolves NO if accidental discharge or ricochet caused something to shoot towards Trump.

*I am using bullet-like projectile to mean something that is for all intents and purposes is a bullet but may not technically be a bullet. For example, I would not count a BB gun pellet since it is not plausibly lethal like a bullet would be.

not_P.title: Did someone not intentionally shoot at Trump on July 13th?
not_P.body:
NYT: "It sounded what could be gun shots interrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was hurried off the stage and appeared to be bleeding by his ear."

Resolves YES if someone did not intentionally shoot a bullet or other bullet-like projectile* at Trump on July 13th. Resolves NO if someone intentionally shot a bullet or other bullet-like projectile at Trump on July 13th.

*I am using bullet-like projectile to mean something that is for all intents and purposes is a bullet but may not technically be a bullet. For example, I would not count a BB gun pellet since it is not plausibly lethal like a bullet would be.

para_P.title: Was there a deliberate shooting at Trump on July 13th?
para_P.body:
According to the NYT: "Sounds resembling gunfire interrupted Trump's rally in Pennsylvania. He was quickly taken off the stage and seemed to be bleeding from his ear."

This resolves to YES if an individual purposefully fired a bullet or a similar projectile at Trump on July 13th. It resolves to NO if the incident was due to an accidental shot or a ricochet that resulted in something being directed towards Trump.

*The term bullet-like projectile refers to anything that functions similarly to a bullet, even if it isn't technically classified as one. For instance, a BB gun pellet wouldn't be included as it is not considered lethal like a bullet.

question.title: Was Trump the target of a deliberate shooting on July 13th?
question.body:
NYT: "Sounds resembling gunfire disrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was quickly escorted off the stage and seemed to have a wound near his ear."

This will resolve to YES if a person aimed and fired a bullet or similar projectile* at Trump on July 13th with intent. It will resolve to NO if the event was caused by an accidental firing or a ricochet that unintentionally directed something towards Trump.

*By bullet-like projectile, I mean an object that functions as a bullet for all practical purposes, though it may not technically be a bullet. For instance, a BB gun pellet wouldn’t count, as it lacks the plausible lethality of a bullet.

not_P.title: Was Trump not the target of a deliberate shooting on July 13th?
not_P.body:
NYT: "Sounds resembling gunfire disrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was quickly escorted off the stage and seemed to have a wound near his ear."

This will resolve to YES if a person did not aim and fire a bullet or similar projectile at Trump on July 13th with intent. It will resolve to NO if the event was caused by an intentional firing that aimed at Trump.

para_P.title: Was Trump intentionally shot at on July 13th?
para_P.body:
According to NYT: "Noises resembling gunfire interrupted Trump’s rally in Pennsylvania. Trump was promptly taken off the stage and appeared to have an injury near his ear."

This will be marked as YES if an individual aimed and discharged a bullet or similar projectile* at Trump on July 13th with purpose. It will be marked as NO if the incident resulted from an accidental discharge or a ricochet that unintentionally directed something towards Trump.

*By bullet-like projectile, I refer to an object that serves the same function as a bullet for all practical purposes, although it may not be technically classified as a bullet. For example, a BB gun pellet would not qualify, as it does not possess the plausible lethality of a bullet.

question.title: Will at least 20 House/Senate Democrats sign a public letter opposing the plan to virtually nominate Biden early?
question.body:
Context from Politico:

Dozens of House Democrats are organizing a plan to speak out against their own party’s effort to seal President Joe Biden’s nomination sooner than originally planned, which they argue stifles the intense ongoing debate about his candidacy, according to a lawmaker involved in the effort.

A drafted letter, circulated by Rep. Jared Huffman (D-Calif.) and obtained by POLITICO, offers the first public signal from Democrats since the weekend’s attempted assassination on former President Donald Trump that scores of their own members remain deeply unsettled about the future of Biden’s candidacy.

“It’s a really bad move by the DNC. Somebody thinks it’s a clever way to lock down debate and I guess by dint of sheer force, achieve unity, but it doesn’t work that way,” Huffman said in an interview. He declined to confirm the existence of a letter.

This market resolves YES if a public letter opposing the early nomination plan is signed by at least 20 House Members or Senators who caucus with the Democratic Party before market close at the end of Sunday, July 21st. 

Multiple such letters with a combined total of 20 lawmaker's signatures would also be sufficient to resolve this market to YES. 

If these criteria are not met by market close, this market resolves NO.

question.title: Will Trump's lead over Biden be greater than 2 and less than or equal to 4 on July 15, 2024, according to 538's national polling average?
question.body:

question.title: Will "Twisters" (2024) have a Rotten Tomatoes critics score of at least 75%? ("Certified Fresh")
question.body:
"Twisters" (2024) Rotten Tomatoes page

This resolves YES if the Tomatometer score is 75% or higher, one week after release (July 26th). 

Details 

I will use whatever precision is listed by Rotten Tomatoes (typically an integer percentage, no decimal).

For example, the original "Twister" (1996) currently has a Tomatometer of 63%. This is the equivalent score I will use.

"Certified Fresh" is just used for illustrative purposes (AFAIK, it requires >=75% Tomatometer, but there might be other restrictions—the market resolves solely based on the displayed score).

"Twisters" (2024) is a standalone sequel to the 1996 original, directed by Lee Isaac Chung ("Minari"), starring Glen Powell ("Top Gun: Maverick") and Daisy Edgar Jones ("Normal People").

question.title: Will Biden be declared incapacitated under the 25th Amendment Section 4 before August?
question.body:
Resolves YES if the Vice President and a majority of the Cabinet (or other relevant body) invokes Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to formally declare that "the President is unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office" and cause the Vice President to serve as Acting President, before August 2024 (Eastern time).

The duration of the incapacity does not matter for this question.

Biden exiting the office of the Presidency by death, resignation, etc does not count. Biden invoking section 3 of the 25th amendment does not count.

Context: GOP lawmaker asks Merrick Garland to invoke 25th Amendment to remove Biden from office

not_P.title: Will Biden not be declared incapacitated under the 25th Amendment Section 4 before August?
not_P.body:
Resolves YES if the Vice President and a majority of the Cabinet (or other relevant body) do not invoke Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to formally declare that "the President is unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office" and do not cause the Vice President to serve as Acting President, before August 2024 (Eastern time).

The duration of the incapacity does not matter for this question.

Biden exiting the office of the Presidency by death, resignation, etc does not count. Biden invoking section 3 of the 25th amendment does not count.

Context: GOP lawmaker does not ask Merrick Garland to invoke 25th Amendment to remove Biden from office.

para_P.title: Will Biden be deemed unfit under Section 4 of the 25th Amendment prior to August?
para_P.body:
Resolves YES if the Vice President along with a majority of the Cabinet (or other pertinent authority) activates Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to officially state that "the President is unable to fulfill the powers and responsibilities of his position" and allows the Vice President to act as President, before August 2024 (Eastern time).

The length of the incapacity is irrelevant to this inquiry.

Biden leaving the presidential office due to death, resignation, etc., is not included. Biden's activation of section 3 of the 25th amendment is also excluded.

Context: A GOP legislator requests Merrick Garland to implement the 25th Amendment to remove Biden from his position.

question.title: Will Biden be deemed unable to fulfill his presidential duties under the 25th Amendment Section 4 before August?
question.body:
This question will resolve as YES if, before August 2024 (Eastern time), the Vice President and a majority of the Cabinet (or another appropriate body) activate Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to officially state that "the President is unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office," resulting in the Vice President assuming the role of Acting President.

The length of the incapacity is irrelevant to this question.

Biden leaving the presidency due to death, resignation, or similar reasons does not qualify. Biden invoking section 3 of the 25th amendment is also not applicable.

Background: A GOP legislator has requested Merrick Garland to use the 25th Amendment to remove Biden from office.

not_P.title: Will Biden be deemed able to fulfill his presidential duties under the 25th Amendment Section 4 before August?
not_P.body:
This question will resolve as YES if, before August 2024 (Eastern time), the Vice President and a majority of the Cabinet (or another appropriate body) do not activate Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to officially state that "the President is unable to discharge the powers and duties of his office," resulting in the Vice President not assuming the role of Acting President.

The length of the incapacity is irrelevant to this question.

Biden leaving the presidency due to death, resignation, or similar reasons does not qualify. Biden invoking section 3 of the 25th amendment is also not applicable.

Background: A GOP legislator has requested Merrick Garland to use the 25th Amendment to remove Biden from office.

para_P.title: Will Biden be considered incapable of carrying out his presidential responsibilities according to Section 4 of the 25th Amendment prior to August?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will be answered with a YES if, before August 2024 (Eastern time), the Vice President along with a majority of the Cabinet (or another relevant authority) enact Section 4 of the 25th Amendment to formally declare that "the President is unable to perform the powers and duties of his office," leading to the Vice President taking on the role of Acting President.

The duration of the incapacity does not affect this question.

Biden's exit from the presidency due to death, resignation, or similar circumstances does not count. Biden's invocation of section 3 of the 25th amendment is also not relevant.

Background: A GOP legislator has urged Merrick Garland to utilize the 25th Amendment to oust Biden from office.

question.title: Will UCLA hold its in-person, university-wide graduation commencement ceremonies scheduled for June 14, 2024?
question.body:
This question resolves as **Yes** if the University of California-Los Angeles (UCLA) holds all three of its main in-person college commencement ceremonies for the graduating Class of 2024 [scheduled](https://commencement.ucla.edu/schedule/ucla-commencement-schedule-alphabetical#college) for the following times and locations on June 14, 2024:

- 11 AM at the Pauley Pavilion
- 3 PM at the Pauley Pavilion
- 7 PM at the Pauley Pavilion

The ceremonies must all occur at the specified locations and begin within 1 hour of the scheduled starting time. 

This question will resolve as **No** if any ceremony either does not begin within an hour of the scheduled time, is moved to another location, or is held entirely online (i.e., without graduates, faculty, and guests attending in person).

question.title: [Metaculus] Will diplomatic expulsions or recalls take place between the Philippines and China before August 1, 2024?
question.body:
Will diplomatic expulsions or recalls take place between the Philippines and China before August 1, 2024?

Resolves the same as the original on Metaculus.

(https://www.metaculus.com/questions/question_embed/24034/?theme=dark)Resolution criteria

This question resolves as Yes if before August 1, 2024, one of these four events happens, according to official statements or credible reports:

The Philippines expels at least one diplomat representing the People's Republic of China (PRC).

The Philippines recalls at least one of its diplomats stationed in the PRC.

The PRC expels at least one diplomat representing the Philippines.

The PRC recalls at least one of its diplomats stationed in the Philippines.

If there are no such reports before that date, then this resolves as No.

question.title: Will Joe Biden announce that he is both dropping out and resigning from the presidency before the end of July?
question.body:
Resolves YES if Joe Biden announces both that he is no longer running for re-election and that he will be resigning and not completing his current term. These announcements before the end of July 2024 in Pacific Time, but he does not have to have formally resigned and be out of office before the end of July. An announcement of his intention to do so is sufficient to resolve this market.

Otherwise, this market resolves NO on August 1st.

An announcement of his intention to do so is sufficient to resolve this market.

Otherwise, this market resolves NO on August 1st.

para_P.body:
This resolves to YES if Joe Biden makes an announcement stating that he is ceasing his campaign for re-election and that he will be resigning from his current presidential term. Such announcements must occur before the end of July 2024, according to Pacific Time, although he is not required to have officially resigned and left office by then. A declaration of his plans to do so will suffice to resolve this market.

If this does not occur, the market will resolve to NO on August 1st.

question.title: Is it true that Joe Biden will declare his withdrawal from the presidential race and his resignation from office by the end of July?
question.body:
This question will resolve as YES if Joe Biden states that he will not seek re-election and will resign, not finishing his present term. The announcement must occur by the end of July 2024, Pacific Time. He doesn't need to have officially resigned by then; merely announcing his intention suffices for a YES resolution.

If not, this question resolves as NO on August 1st.

not_P.body:
This question will resolve as YES if Joe Biden does not state that he will not seek re-election and will not resign, finishing his present term. The announcement must not occur by the end of July 2024, Pacific Time. He doesn't need to have officially resigned by then; merely not announcing his intention suffices for a YES resolution.

If so, this question resolves as NO on August 1st.

para_P.title: Will Joe Biden announce his exit from the presidential race and his resignation from his position before July concludes?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will be deemed TRUE if Joe Biden declares that he will not pursue re-election and will step down, thereby not completing his current term. The declaration must be made by the end of July 2024, Pacific Time. It is not necessary for him to have officially resigned by that time; a mere announcement of his intention is sufficient for a TRUE resolution.

If he does not make such an announcement, this question will be resolved as FALSE on August 1st.

question.title: Will at least 30% of Manifold respondents agree that weak AGI had been achieved before July 23, 2024?
question.body:
[image]Every month, a Manifold poll is being posted to gain the consensus view of progress towards AGI. Unlike many of the markets and questions on Manifold, these polls will simply ask "has weak AGI been achieved," rather than providing a definition of the term. The goal is that given that the term is so broad, the only way to characterize AI progress is also to allow respondents to vote based upon their own understanding.

Progress has been steady.  The previous polls are referenced here:

@/SteveSokolowski/did-openai-achieve-weak-agi-with-gp  (Answer: 15)

@/SteveSokolowski/june-2024-has-weak-agi-been-achieve  (Answer: 27)

The previous markets on this topic, which significantly understimated Manifold's belief in AI progress, were:

@/SteveSokolowski/what-percentage-of-manifold-poll-re 

@/SteveSokolowski/will-at-least-20-of-manifold-respon 

The polls will not reference any specific model, and will not define "AGI" except to state that the poll does not require that the software system be able to manipulate the physical world. The polls open on the 23rd of each month and close on the 30th.

This market will resolve to YES if the July 2024 poll results in a ratio of YES/(NO + YES) greater than or equal to 0.3. The "no opinion" respondents will be ignored. Otherwise, this question will resolve to NO.

See also:

@/SteveSokolowski/will-one-of-the-monthly-has-weak-ag

question.title: Iran military response before August 13th midnight Eastern Time?
question.body:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Iran initiates a military action on Israeli soil, airspace, or maritime territory between July 30 and August 12, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purposes of this market, a "military action" will be considered to be any use of force executed by Iran on Israeli soil, airspace, or maritime territory (e.g. if a weapons depot on Israeli soil is hit by an Iranian missile, this market will resolve to "Yes") that is officially acknowledged by the Iranian government or a consensus of credible reporting. This includes, but is not limited to, airstrikes, naval attacks, or ground invasions. Cyber attacks, sanctions, or diplomatic actions will not count towards the resolution of this market.

Only responses by Iranian forces explicitly claimed by the Islamic Republic of Iran, or confirmed to have originated from Iranian territory will count toward the resolution of this market. Attacks on Israel by proxy forces (i.e. Hezbollah, Houthis, etc.) will not count toward the resolution of this market.

not_P.title: Iran military response before August 13th midnight Eastern Time?
not_P.body:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Iran does not initiate a military action on Israeli soil, airspace, or maritime territory between July 30 and August 12, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to "No".

For the purposes of this market, a "military action" will be considered to be any use of force executed by Iran on Israeli soil, airspace, or maritime territory (e.g. if a weapons depot on Israeli soil is not hit by an Iranian missile, this market will resolve to "Yes") that is not officially acknowledged by the Iranian government or a consensus of credible reporting. This includes, but is not limited to, airstrikes, naval attacks, or ground invasions. Cyber attacks, sanctions, or diplomatic actions will not count towards the resolution of this market.

Only responses by Iranian forces explicitly claimed by the Islamic Republic of Iran, or confirmed to have not originated from Iranian territory will count toward the resolution of this market. Attacks on Israel by proxy forces (i.e. Hezbollah, Houthis, etc.) will not count toward the resolution of this market.

para_P.title: Will Iran take military action before the deadline of August 13th at midnight Eastern Time?
para_P.body:
This market will conclude with a "Yes" if Iran conducts a military operation on Israeli territory, airspace, or maritime zones between July 30 and August 12, 2024, at 11:59 PM ET. If not, it will resolve to "No".

For this market's purposes, a "military operation" refers to any forceful action carried out by Iran against Israeli land, airspace, or maritime zones (for instance, if an Iranian missile strikes a weapons facility in Israel, the market will resolve to "Yes") that is officially recognized by the Iranian authorities or supported by a consensus of reliable reports. This includes, but is not limited to, aerial bombardments, naval strikes, or ground assaults. Cyber warfare, sanctions, or diplomatic measures will not be considered for the resolution of this market.

Only actions taken by Iranian military forces that are explicitly claimed by the Islamic Republic of Iran or confirmed to have originated from Iranian territory will be counted for this market's resolution. Attacks on Israel carried out by proxy groups (such as Hezbollah, Houthis, etc.) will not be included in the resolution of this market.

question.title: Will Iran take military action against Israel by August 13th, Eastern Time?
question.body:
This market will resolve to "Yes" if Iran carries out a military operation in Israeli territory, airspace, or waters between July 30 and August 12, 2024, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, it will resolve to "No".

For the purpose of this market, "military operation" refers to any act of aggression conducted by Iran in Israeli territory, airspace, or waters (e.g., if an Iranian missile strikes a weapons facility on Israeli land, the market will resolve to "Yes") that is officially recognized by the Iranian government or widely reported by credible sources. This includes, but is not limited to, aerial bombardments, naval engagements, or land invasions. Cyber warfare, economic sanctions, or diplomatic efforts are excluded from this market's resolution criteria.

Only actions by Iranian military forces explicitly acknowledged by the Islamic Republic of Iran, or verified to have been launched from Iranian land will be considered for this market's resolution. Attacks on Israel by proxy groups (such as Hezbollah, Houthis, etc.) will not be included in this market's resolution.

not_P.body:

For the purpose of this market, "military operation" refers to any act of aggression conducted by Iran in Israeli territory, airspace, or waters (e.g., if an Iranian missile does not strike a weapons facility on Israeli land, the market will resolve to "Yes") that is not officially recognized by the Iranian government or not widely reported by credible sources. question.title: Will 538 Project Biden as the favorite on Friday?
question.body:
This market will resolve to “Yes” if Joe Biden has a higher probability of winning the US presidential election than Donald Trump according to the FiveThirtyEight election forecast for the day of July 19, 2024. This market will resolve to “No” if Donald Trump has a higher probability of winning the US presidential election than Joe Biden according to the FiveThirtyEight election forecast for the day of July 19, 2024. If Biden and Trump have equal odds, this market will resolve 50-50.

The resolution source will be FiveThirtyEight's 2024 presidential election forecast, https://projects.fivethirtyeight.com/2024-election-forecast/, specifically the numbers indicated by the blue and red trend lines for this market's resolution date. Changes in the methodology by which FiveThirtyEight calculates its figures will have no bearing on the resolution of this market.

This market will resolve according to the datapoints for July 19 as soon as datapoints for July 20 become available. This market may not resolve until the July 20 datapoints are available. If no datapoints for July 19 are available by July 22, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve according to the nearest previous figures to July 19.

Please note the resolution refers to the odds of each candidate winning as a number out of 100 reported to the 1 digit mark (eg. "Trump 57 times out of 100"). The listed number of simulations out of 1,000 won by each candidate will NOT be considered.

If there are no data points for July 19 by July 22, 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve based on the closest preceding figures to July 19.

Please be aware that the resolution pertains to the winning odds of each candidate expressed as a number out of 100 rounded to one decimal place (e.g., "Trump 57 out of 100"). The number of simulations out of 1,000 won by each candidate will not be taken into account.

question.title: Will Biden remain President through end of July 2024?
question.body:
Resolves YES if Biden remains US President through the end of July 2024 (ET); resolves NO if he resigns, dies, or otherwise ceases to be President before then.

Temporary transfer of power under the 25th amendement (i.e. making his VP the Acting President) does not cause a YES resolution. (Acting President is different from President under the Constitution)

not_P.title: Will Biden not remain President through end of July 2024?
not_P.body:
Resolves YES if Biden does not remain US President through the end of July 2024 (ET); resolves NO if he remains President through the end of July 2024. 

Temporary transfer of power under the 25th amendment (i.e. making his VP the Acting President) does not cause a NO resolution. (Acting President is different from President under the Constitution)

para_P.title: Will Biden stay in office until the conclusion of July 2024?
para_P.body:
Resolves YES if Biden is still the US President at the end of July 2024 (ET); resolves NO if he resigns, passes away, or otherwise stops being President prior to that time.

A temporary handover of authority under the 25th amendment (such as appointing his VP as Acting President) does not lead to a YES resolution. (Acting President is distinct from President according to the Constitution)

question.title: Will Biden continue as President until after July 2024?
question.body: The question will be answered YES if Biden stays in his role as US President past the end of July 2024 (ET); it will be answered NO if he steps down, passes away, or otherwise stops being President before that time. A temporary handover of power under the 25th amendment, making the Vice President the Acting President, does not lead to a YES answer, as the Acting President is distinct from the President according to the Constitution.

not_P.title: Will Biden not continue as President until after July 2024?
not_P.body: The question will be answered YES if Biden does not stay in his role as US President past the end of July 2024 (ET); it will be answered NO if he stays in office, does not step down, does not pass away, and otherwise continues being President after that time. A temporary handover of power under the 25th amendment, making the Vice President the Acting President, does lead to a YES answer, as the Acting President is distinct from the President according to the Constitution.

para_P.title: Is it possible for Biden to remain in office as President beyond July 2024?
para_P.body: This question will receive a YES response if Biden remains in his position as the President of the United States after the conclusion of July 2024 (Eastern Time); conversely, it will be NO if he resigns, dies, or otherwise ceases to be President before that date. A temporary transfer of authority under the 25th amendment, which designates the Vice President as the Acting President, does not result in a YES answer, as the Acting President is considered separate from the President according to the Constitution.

question.title: Will Donald Trump be removed or blocked from the primary election ballot of any U.S. state for a federal office under Section 3 of the 14th Amendment?
question.body:
This question will resolve as "Yes" if, *on* July 15, 2024:

Donald Trump has been officially removed or blocked from the primary election ballot of any U.S. state for a federal office (President, Senate, House of Representatives) under the grounds of Section 3 of the 14th Amendment.

The removal or block is confirmed through official state government announcements, court decisions, legal documentation, or credible media reports. Speculative reports, opinion pieces, or unofficial announcements will not suffice for resolution.

The question will resolve as "No" if these conditions are not met as of July 15, 2024.

Note: The question does not account for legal battles, appeals, or subsequent reversals that might occur *after* the mentioned date. It strictly pertains to whether Donald Trump has been removed from any state's primary election ballot for a federal office under the specified grounds as of July 15, 2024. If Trump is removed or blocked from a ballot and then reinstated, such that as of July 15th he is not removed or blocked from any ballot, the question resolves negatively.

Donald Trump has not been officially removed or blocked from the primary election ballot of any U.S. state for a federal office (President, Senate, House of Representatives) under the grounds of Section 3 of the 14th Amendment.

The lack of removal or block is confirmed through official state government announcements, court decisions, legal documentation, or credible media reports. Speculative reports, opinion pieces, or unofficial announcements will not suffice for resolution.

The question will resolve as "No" if these conditions are met as of July 15, 2024.

Note: The question does not account for legal battles, appeals, or subsequent reversals that might occur *after* the mentioned date. It strictly pertains to whether Donald Trump has not been removed from any state's primary election ballot for a federal office under the specified grounds as of July 15, 2024. If Trump is not removed or blocked from a ballot and then is subsequently removed or blocked, such that as of July 15th he is removed or blocked from any ballot, the question resolves negatively.

question.title: Will Nigel Farage be elected as a Member of Parliament in the July 4 2024 UK General Election?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** in the event that in the 2024 UK general election held on July 4, 2024, Nigel Farage is elected as the member of parliament (MP) for any UK constituency. The question will resolve as **No** if this does not occur, unless the general election is cancelled or postponed beyond July 4 2024, in which case the question will be **annulled**.

Resolution should cite credible media reports from the BBC, the Times, the Financial Times, the Guardian, or other major UK news sources; or the official announcement of the returning officer for any constituency in which Nigel Farage is a candidate. 

Farage need not be sworn in as an MP for the question to resolve as **Yes** -- this question resolves on the basis of his election or non-election.

question.title: Will Scotland hold an official, sanctioned referendum on independence before May 3, 2024?
question.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if there is a referendum held in Scotland regarding Scotland's independence from the United Kingdom, and this referendum is held before May 3, 2024.  This referendum may be an "advisory" referendum; that is, it is not necessary for the referendum to have any legally binding effect.

It shall not be deemed resolved by a “wildcat” or “Catalan” style of referendum where the UK government has declined permission for the vote, nor by a vote organised by civil society institutions. A referendum must be deemed to have the consent of the London government

not_P.title: Will Scotland not hold an official, sanctioned referendum on independence before May 3, 2024?
not_P.body:
This question will resolve as **Yes** if there is no referendum held in Scotland regarding Scotland's independence from the United Kingdom, and this referendum is held before May 3, 2024. This referendum may be an "advisory" referendum; that is, it is not necessary for the referendum to have any legally binding effect.

It shall be deemed resolved by a “wildcat” or “Catalan” style of referendum where the UK government has declined permission for the vote, nor by a vote organised by civil society institutions. A referendum must be deemed to have the consent of the London government.

para_P.title: Is there a possibility that Scotland will conduct an officially authorized referendum on independence prior to May 3, 2024?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will be considered resolved as **Yes** if a referendum concerning Scotland's independence from the United Kingdom takes place in Scotland before May 3, 2024. This referendum can be classified as an "advisory" referendum; thus, it does not need to carry any legally binding consequences.

A referendum will not be regarded as resolved by a “wildcat” or “Catalan” type of referendum where permission for the vote has been denied by the UK government, nor by a vote organized by civil society groups. For a referendum to be valid, it must have the approval of the London government.

It will not be considered resolved by a “wildcat” or “Catalan” type of vote where the UK government has not granted permission for the vote, nor by a vote organized by civil society groups. A vote must be considered to have the approval of the London government.

not_P.body:

It will be considered resolved by a “wildcat” or “Catalan” type of vote where the UK government has not granted permission for the vote, or by a vote organized by civil society groups. A vote must not be considered to have the approval of the London government.

para_P.title: Will there be an official and sanctioned referendum on Scotland's independence before May 3, 2024?
para_P.body:

Votes that are deemed as “wildcat” or “Catalan” types, where the UK government has not authorized the vote, or those arranged by civil society organizations will not be counted. The vote must have the endorsement of the London government to be considered valid.

question.title: Will a terrorist act occur in metropolitan France during the 2024 Summer Olympics?
question.body:
The question will resolve as Yes if a terrorist attack in [Metropolitan France](https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolitan_France) injures and/or kills at least one person, other than the terrorist(s), between, and inclusive of, the day of the Opening Ceremony (26 July 2024) and the day of the Closing Ceremony (11 August 2024). The question will resolve as No if the above does not happen.

An event will be considered a 'terrorist attack' if it is described as such by any agency of the State of France, or by the French President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers.

The question will resolve as No if the above does happen.

An event will be considered a 'terrorist attack' if it is described as such by any agency of the State of France, or by the French President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers.

para_P.title: Is it possible for a terrorist incident to take place in metropolitan France during the 2024 Summer Olympics?
para_P.body:
This inquiry will be answered with Yes if there is a terrorist incident in [Metropolitan France](https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metropolitan_France) that results in injury and/or death of at least one individual, excluding the terrorist(s), occurring between the date of the Opening Ceremony (26 July 2024) and the date of the Closing Ceremony (11 August 2024). The answer will be No if this situation does not occur.

An incident will be classified as a 'terrorist incident' if it is labeled as such by any official agency of the State of France, or by the French President, Prime Minister, or a member of the Council of Ministers.
